<headline>Special Weather Statement issued March 19 at 10:02PM EDT  by NWS Boston</headline>
<description>...A strong thunderstorm will impact portions of northwestern
Worcester and northeastern Franklin Counties through 1100 PM EDT...
At 1002 PM EDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm over
Erving, or 7 miles east of Greenfield, moving northeast at 70 mph.
HAZARD...Pea size hail.
SOURCE...Radar indicated.
IMPACT...Little to no impact from hail is expected.
Locations impacted include...
Greenfield, Orange, Winchendon, Montague, Northfield, Bernardston,
Leverett, Erving, Gill, Royalston, Wendell and Warwick.
MAX HAIL SIZE...0.25 IN
MAX WIND GUST...&lt;30 MPH</description>
<instruction>Get indoors when you hear thunder. Do not resume outdoor activities
until at least 30 minutes after the storm has passed.</instruction>
